                <head>199. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Tripartite talks were held in New York September 20–22, following the opening of
                    the 15th Session of the <gloss target="#t_UN1">U.N.</gloss> General Assembly on
                    September 19, with <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Livingston T.
                    Merchant</persName>, Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs; <persName
                        corresp="#p_LC1">Charles Lucet</persName>, Minister of the French Embassy;
                    and <persName corresp="#p_MFH1">Frederick Hoyer-Millar</persName>, British
                    Permanent Under Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs, representing their
                    governments. They met on September 20 to discuss procedural matters; a
                    memorandum of conversation (<gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/1), September 20,
                    summarized their discussion. The following memoranda of conversation summarized
                    their discussions on September 21: <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/12 on
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>; <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/19
                    on Berlin; <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/20 on Japan; <gloss target="#t_MC1"
                        >MC</gloss>/22 on the Caribbean; <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/23 on the
                    Middle East Arms Race; <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/24 on the Middle East;
                        <gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/30 on Africa; and <gloss target="#t_MC1"
                        >MC</gloss>/41 on Southeast Asia. The following memoranda of conversation
                    summarized their discussions on September 22: <gloss target="#t_MC1"
                    >MC</gloss>/25 on <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/26 on a draft resolution on Berlin, tactics in
                    the United Nations, and Soviet tensions. Copies of these documents are in
                    Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 64 D 559, CF 1766.</p>
            </div>
